  <d name="en">
    <xhtml name="short">Process to manage the scanner based referential which is sometimes stored in the header of data files.
</xhtml>
    <d name="parameters">
      <xhtml name="T1_TO_Scanner_Based"/>
      <xhtml name="volume_input"/>
      <xhtml name="new_referential"/>
      <xhtml name="referential_volume_input"/>
    </d>
    <xhtml name="long">This process is especially useful in the case of freesurfer data, to manage raw input data (<tt>mri/orig.nii</tt>) and resampled data (<tt>mri/ori/001.nii</tt>) with correspondance between their coordinate systems.<br/><br/>
This process adds new referentials in the brainvisa manager of transformations and creates a transformation from the volume to the scanner based referential.
<br/><br/>Then, in order to link two scanner based referentials between them, see the 
<a href="bvprocess://MergeReferentials">MergeReferentials</a> process.</xhtml>
  </d>
